  "text": "The presence of pericardial effusion in PAH is associated with increased RA pressure and higher mortality rates; however, previous studies have reported that human patients with relatively small pericardial effusion have similar survival rates to those without effusion. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] According to these results, we speculated that therapy with nicorandil alone or the SPN combination may reduce the formation of pericardial effusion associated with elevated RA pressure, which may result from the significant reduction of RVSP.",
